[{"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "The Senator for Finance BremenS-2149 - St 201S-2149EStG: 13aEStG: 52 / 15EStG: 13a / 1EStG: 13a / 2EStG: 13a / 3EStG: 13a / 4EStG: 13a / 5EStG: 13a / 6EStR: 130a / 1BewG: 52BewG. 61 : 10Determination of the profit from agriculture and forestry according to average rates (\u00a7 13a EStG) 1 Application of \u00a7 13a EStG For financial years beginning after December 31, 1973, the GDL is replaced by the provision of \u00a7 13a EStG (\u00a7 52 para 15 EStG 1974)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "In the case of farmers and foresters who are neither obliged to keep books nor have submitted an application in accordance with Section 13a Paragraph 1 Clause 2 EStG within the preclusive period, the profit is to be determined in accordance with Section 13a Paragraph 2 - 6 EStG if there is a basic amount (Section 13a Paragraph 3 EStG) results in more than DM 0 (Section 127 Paragraph 4 EStR)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "Because of the limits at the beginning and end of the accounting obligation, reference is made to Section 127 (1) EStR 1975"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "If a farmer and forester changes from the determination of profits according to Section 4 (1) EStG, Section 12 GDL or Section 13a EStG to determining profits by comparing operating income and operating expenses, the provisions of Section 19 EStR (profit correction) must be observed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "This also applies if he changes from the surplus calculation to another type of profit determination"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "2 Determination of the profit according to \u00a7 13a Abs 2 - 6 EStG The scheme for the determination of the profit according to average rates results from the form \"Annex ESt 2 L / 3 L (74) - Determination of profit according to \u00a7 13a EStG\""}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "In detail I would like to point out the following: 21 Basic amount The basic amount is to be determined according to \u00a7 13a Abs 3 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "Section 130 a Paragraph 3 EStR 1975 must be observed here"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "The 12 part of the initial value is to be used as the basic amount"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "The initial value includes those in the decisive unit value (\u00a7 13a Paragraph 3 No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "1 sentence 2 and 3 EStG): a) the comparative value for agricultural use including the associated deductions and surcharges according to \u00a7 41 BewG, but excluding special crops, b) the hectare values \u200b\u200bof the lowland, c) the comparative values \u200b\u200bfor special uses i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 13a Paragraph 3 No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "1 c EStG, if the sum of the values \u200b\u200bof these special uses contained in the unit value does not exceed DM 4000"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "These special uses do not include forestry use"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "The allocation of the areas to the individual uses based on the standard value method is also decisive for the determination of profit if the actual use at the beginning of the financial year deviates from this"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "Such deviations can only be taken into account when the unit value is updated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "If parts of the areas or assets included in the initial value are leased, the share of the value attributable to the leased areas or assets is to be excluded when determining the initial value (\u00a7 13a Paragraph 3 No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "3 and 4 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "Are areas or assets i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 13a Paragraph 3 No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "1 a to c EStG, the initial value is to be increased by the proportion of the value attributable to this leased area or assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "The conditions at the beginning of the financial year must be taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "The following must be observed when determining the value: a) If there is a separate comparative or individual yield value for the leased area, this must be applied"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "b) Leased areas in the lowlands are to be considered at 50 DM / ha"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "c) If there is no separate comparative value or individual income value for the leased areas or assets, the value must be derived from the value ratios (hectare value) of the own business"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "There are no concerns if the relevant hectare value is determined in such a way that the overall relevant comparative value for the corresponding property areas - without taking into account any additions or deductions according to \u00a7 41 BewG - is divided by the recorded area"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "d) If the value of the leased land and assets cannot be determined in accordance with the above principles, it must be determined in agreement with the valuation body in accordance with the principles of valuation law"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "e) Are comparative values \u200b\u200bin the relevant unit value for leased areas for asparagus growing (Section 52 BewG), vegetable, flower and ornamental plant cultivation and tree nurseries (Section 61 BewG) as well as for other agricultural and forestry uses (Section 62 Paragraph 1 No. 6 BewG), it must be ensured that the comparative values \u200b\u200bfor agricultural uses allocated to the leased (intensively used) areas and attributed to the owner of the areas must also be applied"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "If areas used for agriculture and forestry are valued as real estate (Section 69 BewG), these areas are to be assessed at the value that would result from the provisions on the valuation of agricultural and forestry assets (Section 13a Paragraph 3 No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "5 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "22 Value of the work done When determining the basic amount, it is assumed that the agricultural and forestry operations are managed exclusively with paid workers"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "Therefore, the value of the work performed by the business owner and his unpaid relatives (Section 10 StAnpG, Section 15 AO 1977) must be added to the basic amount (Section 13a (4) EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "Section 130 a Paragraph 4 - 6 EStR 1975 must be observed here"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "When applying \u00a7 13a Paragraph 4 No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "2 EStG the term \"family members\" is the term \"relatives i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 10 StAnpG (\u00a7 15 AO 1966) \"to be equated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "Any co-operation of the retirees in the company is to be taken into account to an appropriate extent - with the exception of minor work which is not carried out constantly but only consists of making themselves useful on the farm"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "When determining the value of the work for the physical work of the business owner and the relatives who are not employed, only the work that is attributable to the individual uses included in the initial value according to Section 13a (3) EStG is to be taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "If the initial value is a value share for special uses i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 13a Paragraph 3 No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "1 c EStG, because the sum of the comparative or individual income values \u200b\u200ballocated to these special uses does not exceed DM 4000 in total, no reduction in the proportion of full-time employees (VAK) allocated to special uses is required when determining the value of the work performed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "In this case, when determining the maximum VAK to be applied in accordance with Section 13 (4) no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "5 EStG to include the area of \u200b\u200bspecial uses in the relevant area of \u200b\u200bthe maximum permissible number of VAK"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "The value of the physical work performance of the business owner and his relatives employed in the business without an employment contract is, according to \u00a7 13a Para 4 No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "5 EStG to be set at the most with the number of VAKs appropriate for the type and size of the establishment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "For areas of agricultural use, a maximum of 007 VAK per hectare are to be set"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "For the other values \u200b\u200bshown in the relevant unit value of the agricultural and forestry business (Section 13a Paragraph 3 No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "1 b and c EStG), the appropriate number of VAK must be determined in each individual case"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "For the appropriate number of VAK for the business owner and for the relatives employed without an employment contract, paid full-time workers are to be taken into account according to the length of their employment (\u00a7 13a Paragraph 4 No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "5 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "This applies not only to permanently employed workers, but also to temporary workers"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "If a surcharge is to be made for special uses that are not included in the determination of the initial value in accordance with Section 13a, Paragraph 3 of the Income Tax Act, in accordance with Section 13a, Paragraph 6 of the Income Tax Act, the wages and remuneration paid to the paid workers must be divided according to the actual workload of the workers are based on the uses included in the initial value and on the special uses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "As a rule, the information from the taxpayer in Appendix L to the income tax return can be followed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "If the Stpfl do not provide any or obviously incorrect information about the respective share of employment, I ask you to assume, as was previously the case with the GDL, that the workforce is 50 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "distributed between normal agricultural use and special uses, if the actual circumstances do not speak against such a distribution ratio (reference to the order of February 22, 1967 - S-2132 a / S-2149 / S-2150 a - St 21 Annex to lit."}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "When determining the appropriate number of VAK and the value of the work performance for the physical work of the business owner and the relatives who work for free in the business, the same procedure must be followed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "If the simplification rule is not applicable, when dividing the work performance in relation to the different labor requirements, the comments in Felsmann - Income taxation of farmers and foresters - in section C 27 (p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "523), Table 4 on the average labor requirement in special branches of industry serve as a guide"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "23 Value of the work done for the company management The value of the work done for the management of the company is 25% of the basic amount"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "of the initial value determined in accordance with Section 13a (3) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "The amount of 25 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "The full amount of the initial value must also be applied if the company is managed by a person whose physical work performance is not to be taken into account at its full value or to be left entirely out of consideration"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "The value must also be applied in full if the business owner does not manage the business himself or the management is in other hands (e"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "Wife, son, son-in-law)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "If the company is managed by several people, the value only needs to be taken into account once"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "24 Lease interest received Lease interest received, reduced by proportionate operating expenses, are to be added to the basic amount in accordance with Section 13a (5) sentence 3 EStG if they are included in income from agriculture and forestry"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "The prerequisite for this is that the leased areas belong to the agricultural and forestry business assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "Even individually leased areas that are permissibly assigned to business assets remain business assets until they are transferred to private assets through an unambiguous (express or conclusive) withdrawal process (Section 14 (13) EStR)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "If the taxpayer does not declare the operating expenses attributable to the leased land, there are no concerns if they are 25 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "of the comparative value applicable to the leased area"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "If, according to the lease agreement, the lessee has paid the property tax, contributions to the Chamber of Agriculture and similar charges, these amounts are to be recognized as rent received from the lessor"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "25 Surcharges according to Section 13a (6) EStG When determining the average rate profit according to Section 13a EStG, the income from a) special uses i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 13a Paragraph 3 No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "1 c EStG, insofar as these are not already included in the basic amount, b) forestry use, c) other operating processes that were not taken into account when determining the initial value (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "Profits from the sale of breeding cattle, profits from the sale or the removal of land), to be recorded by surcharges, if this increases the amount determined according to \u00a7 13a Paragraph 2 to 5 EStG by at least DM 800"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "The income to be recorded as a surcharge is basically to be determined by comparing the operating income and operating expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "If there are no records, the yields are to be estimated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "The guideline rates to be applied in the estimate for sales and operating income from field vegetable growing, sales and operating income from fruit growing, sales and operating income from the rearing of animals for third parties in the wage system; Sales and profits from keeping sire animals; Additional sales and additional profits from the sale of livestock are announced by special orders"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "If the income is determined by means of an estimate, the expenses for external wages associated with the special uses (if applicable"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "pro rata), lease interest and debt interest to be deducted from operating income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "The surcharges according to Section 13a (6) of the Income Tax Act are to be viewed as a single unit"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "Losses incurred in individual special uses and operations can be offset against profits from other special uses and operations"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "A total loss calculated with this netting cannot lead to a discount (section 130 a, paragraph 8 of the Income Tax Regulation)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "To the income i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "of Section 13a (6) EStG does not include the income from a) field-based cultivation of threshing peas, French beans and cabbage as industrial vegetables, b) tobacco cultivation and c) seed potato cultivation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "26 Value in use of the apartment The value in use of the owner's apartment is to be set at one eighteenth of the apartment value specifically shown in the unit value"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "The residential part includes the buildings and parts of the building insofar as they are used by the owner of the business, the family members belonging to his household and the senior citizens for residential purposes (Section 34 (3) BewG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "If the residential rights of the senior citizens are secured in rem, the value of the apartment is to be reduced proportionally according to the ratio of the living space provided to the total living space"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "There are no concerns that the proportion of senior citizens' apartments in these cases is 25%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "of the flat value shown in the standard value if the actual ratio of the living space cannot be determined from the documents"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "27 Rent paid rent Rent paid out is deductible up to the twelfth part of the initial value for the leased land and parts of the business"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "In the case of residential buildings that have been leased, the rent applicable to them can be deducted up to one eighteenth of the value of the apartment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "Rent payments that are wholly or partially attributable to uses and parts of the business that are excluded from the determination of the initial value (Section 13a Paragraph 3 No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "1 c EStG) are not to be deducted from the basic amount"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "They are to be taken into account as operating expenses when calculating the surcharge (Section 13a (6) EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "The amounts paid that the lessee has to spend on the lease are to be recognized as the rent paid, reduced by the operating expenses covered by the basic amount (pure rent)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "There are no concerns that the operating expenses covered by the basic amount are 25 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "of the value portion contained in the initial value for the leased areas"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "28 Deduction of debt interest and permanent charges Insofar as debt interest represents business expenses, it is unlimited in amount deductible"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "This also applies to interest on the mortgage profit levy"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "Debt interest due on uses and parts of the business, which is excluded when determining the initial value, must be taken into account as business expenses when calculating the surcharge"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "A deduction of permanent burdens, which are business expenses, presupposes according to \u00a7 13a Abs. 2 Satz 2 EStG that these have not been taken into account in the unit valuation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "The usual permanent loads on the farm, such as the dike and sill loads (incl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "the contributions to the water and soil associations), as well as the property tax burden have already been taken into account in the unit assessment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "With regard to the tax treatment of partial retirement benefits, reference is made to the order of July 29, 1975 - S-2230 - St 212"}, {"meta": {"name": "0031064.xml"}, "text": "Accounting income tax / wage tax / church tax assessmentBremen Landwirtschaft luft-e-5"}]